at even functionally identical models yield vastly different attributions, it challenges the semantic validity of current explanation techniques and suggests a need for regularization during interpretation, akin to adversarial training for robustness. Conversely, if attributions align well across equivalent models, instability in standard settings may be attributed to representational drift rather than methodological flaws. This work has broad implications for model trustworthiness in high-stakes domains like healthcare and law, where consistent, reliable explanations are essential.",
